---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import siteConfig from "../data/site-config.json";

/* Methodology page - renders the weighted featureAxes rubric straight from
   site-config.json so the published weights match the per-piece scorecards.
   Voice-clean: states plainly that we do not claim hands-on testing. */
const axes = siteConfig.featureAxes.default;
const total = axes.reduce((sum, a) => sum + a.weight, 0);
---
<MainLayout
  title="How we evaluate retro gear"
  description="The weighted rubric behind every GameOverGear pick: authenticity, compatibility, build quality, value, and ease of setup, plus what we don't claim."
>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc-header">
      <span class="doc-kicker">Methodology</span>
      <h1>How we evaluate retro gear</h1>
      <p class="doc-lede">
        Every pick runs through the same weighted rubric. Here is exactly what we
        weigh, how much each axis counts, and what we deliberately do not claim.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>The rubric</h2>
    <p>
      We score each product on five axes. The weights below add up to {total} and
      are the same weights behind the scorecard on every review.
    </p>

    <div class="rubric">
      {axes.map((axis) => (
        <div class="rubric-row">
          <div class="rubric-row__head">
            <span class="rubric-row__name">{axis.name}</span>
            <span class="rubric-row__weight">{axis.weight}%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rubric-bar" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="rubric-bar__fill" style={`width:${axis.weight}%`}></span>
          </div>
          <p class="rubric-row__desc">{axis.description}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2>What the evidence is</h2>
    <p>
      Scores come from published manufacturer specifications, patterns across
      aggregated verified-buyer reviews, and independent third-party testing
      (teardowns and measured results from outlets like My Life in Gaming,
      RetroRGB, and Modern Vintage Gamer), each cited where we lean on it.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't claim</h2>
    <p>
      We do not claim personal hands-on testing of the products we cover. Our
      content is comparison-and-fit analysis, not first-person reviews. When we
      describe how a controller feels or how a scaler performs, we are reporting
      the spec, the aggregated owner reports, or an independent test, and we say
      which. If you want a first-person review, look for a reviewer who claims one.
    </p>

    <h2>Authenticity and compatibility come first</h2>
    <p>
      GameOverGear ranks the gear, not the game. We focus on how close a product
      gets to the original feel, what consoles and regions it works with, and
      whether it is the buy-once option or the cheap-and-replace one. Those are
      the questions that decide whether a retro purchase was worth it.
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .doc { max-width: var(--content-wide); margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6) var(--space-20); }
  .doc-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .doc-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    color: var(--color-paper-ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .doc-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 58ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .doc h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .doc p { font-family: var(--font-sans); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); max-width: 64ch; color: var(--color-paper-ink); }

  .rubric { margin: var(--space-6) 0; }
  .rubric-row {
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .rubric-row:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .rubric-row__head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .rubric-row__name {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-paper-ink);
  }
  .rubric-row__weight {
    font-family: var(--font-mono, ui-monospace, Consolas, monospace);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-brass);
  }
  .rubric-bar {
    height: 10px;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .rubric-bar__fill {
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--color-brass);
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(46, 230, 255, 0.5);
  }
  .rubric-row__desc {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
